The paper deals with algorithms for maintaining and processing data streams, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The focus on memory usage and worst-case guarantees suggests that information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC) may also be relevant sub-categories. Finally, the specific problems addressed in the paper, such as frequency moments and density estimations, suggest that discrete mathematics (cs.DM) may also be a relevant sub-category.
